# Nexus directory boundary (`components/nexus/`)

Mirrors **AGENTS.md §7 → Design system** (app shell row). **Canonical shell product doctrine:** **[`docs/decisions/0001-afenda-spatial-os-shell.md`](../../docs/decisions/0001-afenda-spatial-os-shell.md)** (Spatial OS — L1 Utility / L2 Workspace / L3 Command–Intent / L4 Dock) and **[`docs/decisions/0005-workbench-canonical-shell.md`](../../docs/decisions/0005-workbench-canonical-shell.md)**. If this rule and `AGENTS.md` diverge, follow `AGENTS.md` and fix this rule in the same PR.

> **`components/nexus/`** is no longer the shell host. Shell chrome (utility bar, command layer, rail, dock, mobile rail) lives in **`components/workbench/`** (see **`.cursor/rules/workbench-directory.mdc`**). **`components/nexus/`** retains only the **Nexus Field product surface** and **Lynx summon UI**.

## Authority

- **`components/nexus/`** retains:
  - **Nexus Field product surface** (`nexus-page.tsx` + zone components: `nexus-orientation-band.tsx`, `nexus-operational-pressure.tsx`, `nexus-pressure-item.tsx`, `nexus-priority-lanes.tsx`, `nexus-truth-map.tsx`, `nexus-recent-resolution.tsx`, `nexus-resolution-strip.tsx`, `nexus-surface-card.tsx`, `nexus-nav-panel.tsx`)
  - **Lynx summon UI** (`nexus-lynx-summon-context.tsx`, `nexus-lynx-summon.client.tsx`, `nexus-lynx-truth-feed.tsx`)
  - Utility widgets not yet migrated to `components/workbench/` — move them in the same PR that touches them
- **`components/workbench/`** owns **all post-login shell chrome** — see **`.cursor/rules/workbench-directory.mdc`**.
- **IAM auth surfaces** (sign-in, interruption flows) use **`components/auth/`** and **`#lib/auth`**.

## Forbidden

- Adding new shell-chrome to `components/nexus/` — shell chrome belongs in `components/workbench/`.
- Re-creating `nexus-shell.tsx` or `nexus-surface-chrome.tsx` — these files have been deleted; `WorkbenchShell` is the replacement.
- Tenant-scoped **ERP/domain logic** inside `components/nexus/**`.
- **Deep imports** into `lib/features/<module>/data/...` from Nexus components — consume `#features/<module>` or `#features/<module>/client` barrels only.
